30 /*
31  * To build applications for older versions of DirectInput
32  *
33  * #define DIRECTINPUT_VERSION [ 0x0300 | 0x0500 | 0x0700 ]
34  *
35  * before #include <dinput.h>. By default, #include <dinput.h>
36  * will produce a DirectX 8-compatible header file.
37  *
38  */
39 
40 #define DIRECTINPUT_HEADER_VERSION 0x0800
41 #ifndef DIRECTINPUT_VERSION
42 #define DIRECTINPUT_VERSION DIRECTINPUT_HEADER_VERSION
43 #pragma message(__FILE__ ": DIRECTINPUT_VERSION undefined. Defaulting to version 0x0800")
44 #endif

2703 /****************************************************************************
2704  *
2705  * Return Codes
2706  *
2707  ****************************************************************************/
2708 
2709 /*
2710  * The operation completed successfully.
2711  */
2712 #define DI_OK S_OK
2713 
2714 /*
2715  * The device exists but is not currently attached.
2716  */
2717 #define DI_NOTATTACHED S_FALSE
2718 
2719 /*
2720  * The device buffer overflowed. Some input was lost.
2721  */
2722 #define DI_BUFFEROVERFLOW S_FALSE
2723 
2724 /*
2725  * The change in device properties had no effect.
2726  */
2727 #define DI_PROPNOEFFECT S_FALSE
2728 
2729 /*
2730  * The operation had no effect.
2731  */
2732 #define DI_NOEFFECT S_FALSE
2733 
2734 /*
2735  * The device is a polled device. As a result, device buffering
2736  * will not collect any data and event notifications will not be
2737  * signalled until GetDeviceState is called.
2738  */
2739 #define DI_POLLEDDEVICE ((HRESULT)0x00000002L)
2740 
2741 /*
2742  * The parameters of the effect were successfully updated by
2743  * IDirectInputEffect::SetParameters, but the effect was not
2744  * downloaded because the device is not exclusively acquired
2745  * or because the DIEP_NODOWNLOAD flag was passed.
2746  */
2747 #define DI_DOWNLOADSKIPPED ((HRESULT)0x00000003L)
2748 
2749 /*
2750  * The parameters of the effect were successfully updated by
2751  * IDirectInputEffect::SetParameters, but in order to change
2752  * the parameters, the effect needed to be restarted.
2753  */
2754 #define DI_EFFECTRESTARTED ((HRESULT)0x00000004L)
2755 
2756 /*
2757  * The parameters of the effect were successfully updated by
2758  * IDirectInputEffect::SetParameters, but some of them were
2759  * beyond the capabilities of the device and were truncated.
2760  */
2761 #define DI_TRUNCATED ((HRESULT)0x00000008L)
2762 
2763 /*
2764  * The settings have been successfully applied but could not be
2765  * persisted.
2766  */
2767 #define DI_SETTINGSNOTSAVED ((HRESULT)0x0000000BL)
2768 
2769 /*
2770  * Equal to DI_EFFECTRESTARTED | DI_TRUNCATED.
2771  */
2772 #define DI_TRUNCATEDANDRESTARTED ((HRESULT)0x0000000CL)
2773 
2774 /*
2775  * A SUCCESS code indicating that settings cannot be modified.
2776  */
2777 #define DI_WRITEPROTECT ((HRESULT)0x00000013L)
2778 
2779 /*
2780  * The application requires a newer version of DirectInput.
2781  */
2782 #define DIERR_OLDDIRECTINPUTVERSION \
2783  MAKE_HRESULT(SEVERITY_ERROR, FACILITY_WIN32, ERROR_OLD_WIN_VERSION)
2784 
2785 /*
2786  * The application was written for an unsupported prerelease version
2787  * of DirectInput.
2788  */
2789 #define DIERR_BETADIRECTINPUTVERSION \
2790  MAKE_HRESULT(SEVERITY_ERROR, FACILITY_WIN32, ERROR_RMODE_APP)
2791 
2792 /*
2793  * The object could not be created due to an incompatible driver version
2794  * or mismatched or incomplete driver components.
2795  */
2796 #define DIERR_BADDRIVERVER \
2797  MAKE_HRESULT(SEVERITY_ERROR, FACILITY_WIN32, ERROR_BAD_DRIVER_LEVEL)
2798 
2799 /*
2800  * The device or device instance or effect is not registered with DirectInput.
2801  */
2802 #define DIERR_DEVICENOTREG REGDB_E_CLASSNOTREG
2803 
2804 /*
2805  * The requested object does not exist.
2806  */

2809

2811  * The requested object does not exist.
2812  */

2814  MAKE_HRESULT(SEVERITY_ERROR, FACILITY_WIN32, ERROR_FILE_NOT_FOUND)
